---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Pre-Purchase Termite Inspection Checklist Darwin | Buyer's Guide | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Buying a Top End home? Don't skip the termite inspection. This 11-point pre-purchase checklist tells you what to ask, what to read, and what to negotiate on if the inspection finds issues.">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://darwintermitebarriers.com.au/pre-purchase-checklist/">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">For Greater Darwin home buyers</span>
      <h1>Pre-purchase termite inspection <span class="accent">checklist</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Most NT home contracts include a building-and-pest subject-to clause.
        This is your one chance to get a proper read on a 30-year-old Darwin,
        Palmerston or Litchfield home before you commit. Don&rsquo;t waste it on
        a $99 walkthrough.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book pre-purchase</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>The 11-point buyer&rsquo;s checklist.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Before booking:</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Confirm inspector is NT Pest Control licensed.</strong> All NT pest controllers must hold Pest Management Licence (look up at the NT Government Pest Management licence register). Some operators license-skirt by employing licensed inspectors but the actual person attending is not.</li>
          <li><strong>Confirm inspection follows AS 4349.3.</strong> Australian standard for pre-purchase pest inspections. Should be explicitly listed in the inspector&rsquo;s service description.</li>
          <li><strong>Confirm written report within 24 hours.</strong> Verbal reports are not contractually binding. You need it in writing for your solicitor.</li>
          <li><strong>Confirm photos included.</strong> 20&ndash;40 photos for a typical home, covering every issue and every area inspected.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">During the inspection (be there if possible):</h3>
        <ol start="5">
          <li><strong>Ask the inspector to walk through findings on-site.</strong> Photos and report are great; on-site explanation is gold. Ask about anything you don&rsquo;t understand.</li>
          <li><strong>Ask about access limitations.</strong> What couldn&rsquo;t be inspected? Was the sub-floor accessible? Roof void? Sealed-off areas?</li>
          <li><strong>Ask about conducive conditions specifically.</strong> Not just &ldquo;any termites?&rdquo; but &ldquo;what would attract them here?&rdquo;</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Reading the report:</h3>
        <ol start="8">
          <li><strong>Look at the limitations section first.</strong> The report&rsquo;s legal force is limited to what was actually inspected.</li>
          <li><strong>Check for prior treatment evidence.</strong> Does the property have a Certificate of Termite Protection? When was the last treatment? Is the barrier within its warranty period?</li>
          <li><strong>Check for evidence of past damage.</strong> Old galleries, abandoned mud leads, repaired or replaced structural timber. Past activity isn&rsquo;t a deal-breaker but indicates ongoing risk profile.</li>
          <li><strong>Check the overall risk rating.</strong> Most reports use Low/Medium/High overall risk. High-risk properties need to be priced accordingly OR have a treatment system installed as part of the purchase.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>What &ldquo;findings&rdquo; mean for your purchase decision.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Pure clean &mdash; no active activity, no past damage, good conditions:</h3>
        <p>Proceed. No price adjustment needed.</p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Conducive conditions only (no active or past damage):</h3>
        <p>Proceed with conditions noted. Negotiate $1K&ndash;$3K credit to fix conducive conditions post-settlement.</p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Past damage, no current activity:</h3>
        <p>Negotiate structural repair quote ($3K&ndash;$20K typical). Treat as a known cost. Get full treatment installed (chemical + baiting combined) before moving in.</p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Active current termite activity:</h3>
        <p>Negotiate seller treatment + structural repair before settlement. OR negotiate $8K&ndash;$30K price reduction. OR walk away. Don&rsquo;t buy with active termites unresolved &mdash; ongoing liability.</p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Structural damage:</h3>
        <p>Get a separate structural engineer&rsquo;s assessment ($1,500&ndash;$2,200) before proceeding. Damage may be cosmetic or may indicate replace-the-roof-frame work.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>The Top End-specific risks.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <p>Properties at higher pre-purchase termite risk in Greater Darwin:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>1985&ndash;2005 builds:</strong> earliest with mandatory barrier systems, but many barriers now beyond their warranty period</li>
          <li><strong>Pre-1985 builds:</strong> often no barrier system at all; check carefully</li>
          <li><strong>Canal estates (Howard Springs, Humpty Doo, Paradise Point):</strong> high water table = moist soil = preferred termite habitat</li>
          <li><strong>Acreage / hinterland (Howard Springs, Humpty Doo, Berry Springs):</strong> mature vegetation, wooded surrounds, often outside annual-inspection regimes</li>
          <li><strong>Beachside fixed-frame timber homes:</strong> particularly vulnerable to weather-driven decay AND termite combined</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Where we work.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/palmerston/">Palmerston</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/casuarina/">Casuarina</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/nightcliff/">Nightcliff</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/humpty-doo/">Humpty Doo</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/howard-springs/">Howard Springs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/greater-darwin/">All Greater Darwin</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Pre-purchase termite inspection from $280.</h2>
        <p>2&ndash;3 hour on-site, written report in 24 hours, advice you can take to your solicitor.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book inspection</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
